heblich verschärften.  aIn 1980, those voices calling for moral guidance in the United States could no longer be ignored. Yet from what fiber was this demand for a »moral leader« knitted? Felix Kramer restructures messages and media for the contemporary history of the U.S. and locates a crucial driving force for discursive change in a dynamic television public. Based on evening news from ABC, CBS, and NBC, it depicts the struggles in an intersectional gender ordering, from different liberation movements of the late 1960s to an alleged crisis of U.S. masculinity to the growing influence of the white evangelical movement. His study shows how politicians became preacher figures while cultural conflicts of resource distribution in the 1980s intensified simultaneously.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Nov 2021) 4aAmerika. 4aAmerikanische Geschichte. 4aGeschichte des 20. Jahrhunderts. 4aGeschichtswissenschaft. 4aMedien. 4aMännlichkeit. 4aPolitik. 4aReligion. 4aUSA. 4aZeitgeschichte. 7aHISTORY / United States / General.2bisacsh  aAmerica.  aAmerican History.  aContemporary History.  aHistory of the 20th Century.  aHistory.  aMedia.  aPolitics.  aReligion.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus eBook-Package 2015z978311070098508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2015z9783110439687oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE History 2015z9783110438635oZDB-23-DEG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe Gruyterttranscript Complete eBook Package 2014-2016z9783110489842oZDB-23-TGP08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe Gruyterttranscript: Complete eBook-Package 2014z9783110401226oZDB-23-TGP40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/transcript.9783839426456zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/